title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1991-09-18
lineage: 16 bit 48kHz DAT Master > TASCAM DA-20 (SPDIF out) ->  LynxTWO-B Audio Reference Interface (SPDIF in) ->  Wavelab 6.0 by Todd Evans (todd@bluedakota.com) October 30, 2008   Editing and Mastering: Jamie Waddell (shnflac@gmail.com) on the GEMS Edit Station.  Weiss Saracon for 16 BIT 44.1kHz SRC and POWR-3 Dither  Encoding by Dazed64. Tracked in CDwave, FLAC with Flac Frontend level 8 Tag & Rename for FLAC Meta-Tagging
description:
Set 1

In The Midnight Hour 
Ramble On Rose 
Wang Dang Doodle 
Candyman 
Stuck Inside Of Mobile With The Memphis Blues Again 
Row Jimmy 
Jack Straw 

Set 2

Victim Or The Crime ->
Crazy Fingers ->
Playing In The Band ->
Terrapin Station ->
Drums ->
Space ->
The Wheel ->
I Need A Miracle ->
Wharf Rat ->
Sugar Magnolia 

Encore
Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text: Really clean audience tape Good show; MSG and the Dead were joined at the hip.   Very nice audience tape.  First set spoils us with three lesser played songs  --  Midnight Hour, Wang Dang Doodle, and Stuck in Mobile.  Can't go wrong with an encore like Brokedown Palace.
Best Aud source Nice sound. Solid show
